Euro Declines Against Dollar After Moody's Downgrades Greece Three Grades

-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 
2011-03-07T08:19:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/euro-declines-against-dollar-after-moody-s-downgrades-greece-three-grades.html
The euro declined against the
dollar, snapping three days of gains, after Moody’s Investors
Service downgraded Greek government debt.  The 17-nation currency fell by 0.2 percent to $1.3966 as of
8:16 a.m. in  London , its first decline since March 1. It
weakened for a second day against the yen, losing 0.3 percent to
114.82 yen.  Moody’s downgraded  Greece ’s debt to B1 from Ba1 and
assigned it a negative outlook, the company said in a statement
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in Edinburgh at 
